01N2.statement:
\begin{reference}
\cite[II, Proposition 2.8.10]{EGA}
\end{reference}
With hypotheses and notation as in Lemma @[01MY] above.
Assume there exists a ring map $R \to A_0$ and a ring map
$R \to R'$ such that $B = R' \otimes_R A$. Then
\begin{enumerate}
\item $U(\psi) = Y$,
\item the diagram
$$
\xymatrix{
Y = \text{Proj}(B) \ar[r]_{r_\psi} \ar[d] &
\text{Proj}(A) = X \ar[d] \\
\Spec(R') \ar[r] &
\Spec(R)
}
$$
is a fibre product square, and
\item the maps $\theta : r_\psi^*\mathcal{O}_X(n) \to \mathcal{O}_Y(n)$
are isomorphisms.
\end{enumerate}
